Framing the Issues. 1 of 2. Domestication of Plants and Animals in Global Perspective. The Middle East was the first place where people domesticated plants (ca. 8300 BCE) and animals (ca. 7500 BCE), ushering in the Neolithic period with its characteristic village economies based on food production.
